'''Kuninazu no Ōkashima no Mikoto''' (国摩大鹿島命) was an ancient Japanese noble of the {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft}} and an ancestor of the {{ill|Nakatomi clan|ja|中臣氏|qq=draft}}.
== Overview == Kuninazu no Ōkashima no Mikoto is mentioned in the *{{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft}}* during the 25th year of the reign of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|qq=draft}} as one of the "Five Daibu" (五大夫), prominent nobles of the era. He is listed alongside {{ill|Takeninukawawake|ja|武渟川別|qq=draft}}, the ancestor of the {{ill|Abe clan|ja|阿部氏|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Hikokunifuki|ja|彦国葺|qq=draft}}, the ancestor of the {{ill|Wani clan|ja|和珥氏|qq=draft}}, solidifying his position as a significant figure in early Japanese history.
== Genealogy == Kuninazu no Ōkashima no Mikoto is identified as the son of {{ill|Kushiugatsu no Mikoto|ja|久志宇賀主命|qq=draft}} and the father of {{ill|Omi Sayama no Mikoto|ja|臣狭山命|qq=draft}}, according to genealogical records.<ref>*{{ill|Sonpi Bunmyaku|ja|尊卑分脈|qq=draft}}</ref>
