'''Kuninazu no Ōkashima no Mikoto''' (国摩大鹿島命) was an ancient Japanese noble of the [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]] and an ancestor of the [[:en:Nakatomi clan|Nakatomi clan]].
== Overview == Kuninazu no Ōkashima no Mikoto is mentioned in the *[[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]* during the 25th year of the reign of [[:en:Emperor Suinin|Emperor Suinin]] as one of the "Five Daibu" (五大夫), prominent nobles of the era. He is listed alongside {{ill|Take Nunokawa Wake no Mikoto|lt=Take Nunokawa Wake no Mikoto|lt=Takeninukawawake|ja|武渟川別|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeninukawawake|qq=}}, the ancestor of the {{ill|Abe clan|ja|阿部氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Abe clan|qq=}}, and {{ill|Hikokunifuki|ja|彦国葺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikokunifuki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 彦国葺命}}, the ancestor of the [[:en:Wani clan|Wani clan]], solidifying his position as a significant figure in early Japanese history.
== Genealogy == Kuninazu no Ōkashima no Mikoto is identified as the son of {{ill|Kushiugatsu no Mikoto|ja|久志宇賀主命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kushiugatsu no Mikoto|qq=}} and the father of {{ill|Omi Sayama no Mikoto|ja|臣狭山命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Omi Sayama no Mikoto|qq=}}, according to genealogical records.<ref>*[[:en:Sonpi Bunmyaku|Sonpi Bunmyaku]]</ref>
